'''圣约翰座堂'''（St. John's Cathedral）是美国[[加州|加州]][[洛杉矶市中心|洛杉矶市中心]]附近的一个圣公会教堂，圣公会洛杉矶教区的[[主教座堂|主教座堂]]。

圣约翰堂创立于1890年，为新哥特式。<ref>{{cite news|title=St. John's Church: Laying of the Corner Stone of the New Edifice Yesterday|publisher=Los Angeles Times|date=1890-09-24|url=http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/318313802.html?dids=318313802:318313802&FMT=AI&FMTS=ABS:AI&type=historic&date=Sep+24%2C+1890&author=&pub=The+Los+Angeles+Times+(1886-Current+File)&desc=ST.+JOHN%27S+CHURCH.}}</ref>1894年6月献堂<ref>{{cite news|title=St. John's Church: It Is Consecrated by Bishop Nichols; Assisted by Dean Restarick and the Episcopal Clergy; Impressive Services with a Special Musical Programme; The Ceremony Witnessed by a Congregation that Filled the Sacred Edifice to the Doors -- Beautiful  Floral Decorations|publisher=Los Angeles Times|date=1894-06-11|url=http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/323505072.html?dids=323505072:323505072&FMT=AI&FMTS=ABS:AI&type=historic&date=Jun+11%2C+1894&author=&pub=The+Los+Angeles+Times+(1886-Current+File)&desc=ST.+JOHN%27S+CHURCH.}}</ref>。

1913年-1951年，乔治·戴维森牧师主持该堂期间，信徒从400人增至2,300人。<ref name=Retire>{{cite news|title=Rev. Davidson Will Retire Oct. 1|publisher=Los Angeles Times|date=1951-09-03|url=http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/425188231.html?dids=425188231:425188231&FMT=AI&FMTS=ABS:AI&type=historic&date=Sep+3%2C+1951&author=&pub=Los+Angeles+Times+(1886-Current+File)&desc=REV.+DAVIDSON+WILL+RETIRE+OCT.+1}}</ref> <ref name=Farewell>{{cite news|title=Dr. Davidson in St. John's Farewell After 38 Years: Recalling Fond Relationships of Past, Rector Expresses Gratitude to Church Congregation|publisher=Los Angeles Times|date=1951-10-01|url=http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/425285111.html?dids=425285111:425285111&FMT=AI&FMTS=ABS:AI&type=historic&date=Oct+1%2C+1951&author=&pub=Los+Angeles+Times+(1886-Current+File)&desc=Dr.+Davidson+in+St.+John%27s+Farewell+After+38+Years}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Dr. Davidson; Church Rector for 38 Years|publisher=Los Angeles Times|date=1967-07-19|url=http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/511951062.html?dids=511951062:511951062&FMT=AI&FMTS=ABS:AI&type=historic&date=Jul+19%2C+1967&author=&pub=Los+Angeles+Times+(1886-Current+File)&desc=Dr.+Davidson%3B+Church+Rector+for+38+Years}}</ref>于是在1924-1925年，建造了目前的罗马复兴建筑。1925年献堂时，《时代》周刊称之为全国最美丽和最昂贵的建筑之一<ref name=Newest>{{cite news|title=Newest Church Consecrated: Episcopalians Hold Service in Beautiful Edifice; Choir of Sixty Voices Sings at St. John's Opening; Building Result of Efforts of Dr. George Davidson|publisher=Los Angeles Times|date=1922-12-22|url=http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/358057972.html?dids=358057972:358057972&FMT=AI&FMTS=ABS:AI&type=historic&date=Dec+22%2C+1924&author=&pub=Los+Angeles+Times+(1886-Current+File)&desc=NEWEST+CHURCH+IS+CONSECRATED}}</ref>。另一份报告也指出，是洛杉矶最美丽的建筑<ref name=Blessed>{{cite news|title=Church to be Blessed Today: New Mexico Bishop to Conduct Rites at St. John's; Building is Done in Sixth Century Italian; Has Chapel Dedicated to the World War Veterans|publisher=Los Angeles Times|date=1925-02-03|url=http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/394332721.html?dids=394332721:394332721&FMT=AI&FMTS=ABS:AI&type=historic&date=Feb+3%2C+1925&author=&pub=Los+Angeles+Times+(1886-Current+File)&desc=CHURCH+TO+BE+BLESSED+TODAY}}</ref>。建堂费用65万美元，被描述为六世纪意大利教堂的副本。

在1924年新教堂开幕时，圣约翰堂信徒名单上有2000人，是芝加哥以西最大的圣公会。

该堂活跃于反战运动。

该堂在2000年被列入[[国家史迹名录|国家史迹名录]]。
